ian tiger mosquitoes, which feed on humans and spread the virus.\", \"from\": 4543, \"to\": 4692, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4580, \"end\": 4585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999996257429, \"rank\": 3.743822692887341e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4626, \"end\": 4648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aedes_albopictus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Asian tiger mosquitoes\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aedes_albopictus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aedes_albopictus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Dengue detectives\", \"from\": 4544, \"to\": 4561}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 4595, \"to\": 4607}, {\"ngram\": \"an eye\", \"from\": 4616, \"to\": 4622}, {\"ngram\": \"humans\", \"from\": 4664, \"to\": 4670}, {\"ngram\": \"the virus\", \"from\": 4682, \"to\": 4691}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's true the Olympic Games are a critical moment.\", \"from\": 4694, \"to\": 4745, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 4705, \"to\": 4722}, {\"ngram\": \"a critical moment\", \"from\": 4727, \"to\": 4744}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are prioritising our surveillance in places that will host large gatherings.\", \"from\": 4746, \"to\": 4825, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our surveillance\", \"from\": 4766, \"to\": 4782}, {\"ngram\": \"places\", \"from\": 4786, \"to\": 4792}, {\"ngram\": \"large gatherings\", \"from\": 4808, \"to\": 4824}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is where risk of transmission is highest,\\\" C\\u00e9cile Somarriba, director of health monitoring and safety at the Greater Paris Regional Health Agency (ARS), told The Telegraph.\", \"from\": 4826, \"to\": 5003, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4940, \"end\": 4953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_metropol